    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Farnborough Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Dec. 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I am <hi rend="underline">much</hi> obliged for your note of the 16<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. The Ray Soc<hi rend="superscript">y</hi>. has already given me 22 copies,<ref target="#foot.f1"/> so I have no cause to complain. Should you hear of any copy on sale will you be so kind as to immediately inform me of the Price.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.2 on sale] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi></note>
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.3 immediately] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi></note>
                </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-1472A.xml" resp="#automat">letter to Edwin Lankester, 30 January [1852]</ref>. In that letter only twenty presentation copies were mentioned. CD’s list of presentation copies also indicates that twenty copies were available (MS attached to CD’s copy of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4838.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Living Cirripedia</hi> (1854)</ref> in the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_795.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Cambridge University</ref> Library). The twenty-two copies referred to here may include those due to CD as a subscriber to the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3945.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Ray Society</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3945.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Ray Society</ref> publications were sold by subscription and not through booksellers. A list of subscribers was usually bound into the backs of <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3945.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Ray Society</ref> volumes.</note>
        </div>        
            
